Reasoning: The paper deals with topics related to discrete mathematics, graph theory, and computational complexity, which are all covered by the cs.DM sub-category. The use of symbolic ultrametrics and tree representations suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS). The discussion of cographs and their cotree representations is a classic topic in graph theory (cs.CG). The problem of finding an optimal cograph edge decomposition is related to graph theory and combinatorial optimization (cs.GT). Finally, the NP-completeness result suggests a connection to computational complexity theory (cs.CC).
